---
title: Bacon & Caramelized Onion Omelet with Sourdough Toast, Mixed Greens Salad & Dijon Vinaigrette
description: One bite of this egg-squisite omelet, and you’ll fall in love with eggs all over again! First, you’ll roast bacon until crispy. Then, you’ll caramelize onion until perfectly jammy. Now comes the big moment—and it’s not as tricky as you might think: Just add eggs beaten with crème fraîche to the bubbly butter in your pan, cover with a lid, and voila! In 5 minutes, a fluffy omelet is ready to fold over a hearty filling of bacon, cheddar, and those sweet, sweet onions. Crisp, buttered sourdough toast and a refreshing mixed green salad tossed with marinated tomatoes round out this elegant brunch-inspired meal.
